.SH BUGS
.IP \(bu 2
No rate limit on
.BR /api/auth/login .
A credential-stuffing attacker can probe indefinitely. The
mitigation is the reverse proxy's rate limit (see
.BR reverse-proxy.md ).
.IP \(bu
No rate limit on
.BR /api/auth/register .
The endpoint is admin-only, so the surface is smaller, but a
compromised admin credential can be used to create unlimited
user accounts. Same mitigation.
.IP \(bu
.B SessionAuthFilter
does not set
.B Cache-Control: no-store
on authenticated responses. The
.B X-Session-Id
header is the only auth credential, but a caching proxy that
ignores Vary could in theory serve a previous user's data. The
mitigation is the same reverse proxy.
.IP \(bu
Audit retention is fire-and-forget (see
.BR "AUDIT LOG AND RETENTION" ).
A broken
.B audit_log
table is logged at WARN but does not block user CRUD. Operators
should monitor the JSONL log for
.B AdminAudit
WARN events.
.IP \(bu
The drift check between
.B docs/openapi.yaml
and the live springdoc snapshot is intentionally narrow
(paths, methods, operationIds only). It does not check schemas,
parameters, requestBody, responses, or descriptions, so the
hand-written file can drift from the live implementation in
those dimensions. The OpenAPI spec, the live test suite, and
the implementation are the canonical sources for the rich
shape.
